======================================
CodeIgniter - minify

Simple CodeIgniter library to compress CSS and JavaScript files on the fly.

by Slawomir Jasinski
======================================

Hey everybody,

Library is based on few other scripts like http://code.google.com/p/minify/ and it uses
Google Closure API

DOCUMENTATION:
Documentation is located at http://www.spidersoft.com.au/projects/codeigniter-minify/

INSTALLATION:
Just put minify.php file in libraries path, and proper config file.

USING THE LIBRARY:
Create and compress CSS files, define name of compresesed file:

 1. Easy way:

 Configure the library:
 	$config['assets_dir'] = 'theme/build'; // output path where the compiled files will be stored
	$config['css_dir'] = 'theme/css'; // where to look for css files 
	$config['js_dir'] = 'theme/js'; // where to look for js files

Run the library
 $this->load->library('minify'); //load the library
 $this->minify->css(array('reset.css', 'style.css', 'tinybox.css')); // add css files
 $this->minify->js(array('html5.js','main.js')); // add js files
 $this->minify->deploy_css(true); // bool argument for rebuild css (false means skip rebuilding). Outputs '<link href="path-to-compiled-css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />'.
 $this->minify->deploy_js(true); // bool argument for rebuild js (false means skip rebuilding). Outputs '<script type="text/javascript" src="path-to-compiled-js"></script>'.

Both deploy functions will return the strings to 

compress and display compressed file with link
 echo $this->minify->deploy_css(true);

Feel free to send me an email if you have any problems.


